                    <div id="panelLinks" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="panelHeadingLinks">
                        <div class="panel-body">
                            
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="https://github.com/Esukhia/derge-kangyur" target="ekangyur">eKangyur</a>: A digital Kangyur prepared by Esukhia. To access text files, first select the folder named "derge-kangyur-tags." File numbers correspond to volumes of the Degé Parpü (sde dge par phud) edition of the Kangyur. After selecting a volume click the "View Raw" link. A detailed explanation of the eKangyur version can be found on the home page or by opening the README.md link.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://www.digitaltibetan.org/index.php/Digital_Tibetan" target="digitaltibetan">Digital Tibetan</a>: A fantastic support wiki for working with Tibetan digitally, with links to resources and tools along with up-to-date news on the latest developments.</li>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://resources.84000-translate.org/" target="resources">Restricted Resources for 84000 Translators</a>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://84000.co/resources/other-resources/" target="other-resources">Other Web Resources</a>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="https://www.tbrc.org/#!specials/resources" target="tbrc-resources">Resources for Translators at TBRC</a>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <a href="http://www.buddism.ru/ocr/" target="buddism-ocr">Tibetan OCR</a>: Convert PDF, TIFF, or JPG images into editable and searchable text. Also supports Sanskrit.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                            
